gomodel:SYNGO_5250  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: Sigma-1 receptor (SIGMAR1) knockdown inhibits synapse formation in cultured hippocampal neurons.\n\"In general, silencing of Sig-1R expression increased the length of protrusions by 59% on DIV 16 and 159% on DIV 22, respectively. These results suggest a dysregulation of stage-dependent signalings for actin compartmentalization/polymerization in Sig-1R-deficient neurons.\"\n\nFigure 2: Sigma-1 receptor knockdown inhibits activation of Rac1 Rho GTPase.\n\nFigure 4: Caspase-3-Resistant TIAM1 construct rescues the spine formation in Sigma-1 receptor knockdown neurons.. Experimental description: suppl. M&M: \"Cell culture, transfection, and immunocytochemistry\n Primary hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from rat fetuses at embryonic day\n18-19 according to previously established protocols\"\n\nconstructs:\n\"Production of AAV vectors expressing siCon and siSig-1R AAV vectors containing either the U6 promoter-driven Sig-1R siRNA or the U6 promoter-driven siRNA control were constructed as follows. The siRNA sequences were amplified by PCR with the siRNA expressing pSIREN-Shuttle vector as templates (4). The following primers were used -AAV6-RNAi-F (5' ACGCGTCCCGAAAAGTGCCACCTGAC 3') and - AAV6-RNAi-R (5' ACGCGTTTACCTCTTTCTCCGCACCC 3') to create MluI sites at both ends.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5250" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

